com.daniily.util

Class Tree.Node<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.daniily.util.Tree.Node<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - - class to use
    Enclosing class:
    Tree<E>

    private class Tree.Node<E>
extends java.lang.Object
    Inner class which implements a Node.

    Node is a 'cell' which has an object in it and links with some other nodes: each node has parent (except for root) and can have children. Nodes without children are called 'leaves', first node without a parent is 'root', children of the same node are 'siblings'.
